Sugar is the core of the OLPC Human Interface. The toolkit provides
a set of widgets to build HIG compliant applications and interfaces
to interact with system services like presence and the datastore.


Usage
=====

In order to use this library without installing :

First you need to build sugar and install into a dir:
```
git clone git@github.com:h4ck3rm1k3/sugar.git
./autogen.sh  --prefix=`pwd`/dist
make install
mkdir ~/schemas/
cp dist/share/glib-2.0/schemas/gschemas.compiled ~/schemas/
```

datastore service
=================
Needs datastore service :

  git clone https://src.sugarlabs.org/sugar-datastore/mainline  sugar-datastore
  cd sugar-datastore
  make
  make install
  cd dist/
  PYTHONPATH=~/experiments/osm/sugar-toolkit-gtk3/src/:./lib/python2.7/site-packages/ ./bin/datastore-service 

PYTHONPATH=~/experiments/osm/sugar-toolkit-gtk3/src/:./lib/python2.7/site-packages/ ./bin/datastore-service 


Running example Paint App :
===========================
git clone gitorious@git.sugarlabs.org:~h4ck3rm1k3/paint/h4ck3rm1k3s-paint.git
```
GSETTINGS_SCHEMA_DIR=~/schemas/ PYTHONPATH=~/sugar-toolkit-gtk3/src/ SUGAR_LOGGER_LEVEL=10 SUGAR_BUNDLE_PATH=~/paint-activity python  ./bin/sugar-activity   OficinaActivity.OficinaActivity
```

